The following Venn diagram shows set X and Y inside the universal set, U. What is the complement of Y?
A Venn diagram with a universal set.
A Venn diagram with universal set Upper U contains two intersecting circles labeled Upper X and Upper Y that divide Upper U into four regions. There are values in each region as follows, where the location of the region is given first and the content is given second: Upper X only, Maria, Ana; Upper X and Upper Y only, Karla; Upper Y only, Lucia, Emma; outside the circles only, Mariana, Pilar.

Select the correct answer below:


Yc={Lucia,Karla,Emma}
Yc={Mariana,Pilar}
Yc={Maria,Ana,Mariana,Pilar}
Yc={Maria,Ana,Karla}
